&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scheduled and Planned Care Network&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team: Assessment and Treatment Service, Firshill Rise &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inpatient Learning Disability Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sheffield Health and Social Care NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cook/Housekeeper&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Band 2 £18,005 - £19,337pa pro rata (dependant on experience)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Firshill Rise&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: 25hrs Hours per Week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post Ref: 457-20-019-AN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ATS is a 7 bedded 24/7 specialist inpatient unit for people with a learning disability, autism who are displaying complex needs which may be due to deterioration in mental health and/or challenging behaviours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a committed and enthusiastic individual interested in joining us as a Cook/Housekeeper at Assessment and Treatment Service (ATS), Firshill Rise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working in the housekeeper team on ATS ward to help maintain high standards of cleanliness and hygiene on the ward. This may include daily cleaning rotas, waste management, laundry management and stock control. You will also be preparing, presenting and managing meals on the ward. As a cook / housekeeper you will be expected to have a working knowledge of various health and safety legislation which is pertinent to the role&lt;/p&gt;
